options.content: # General - Hover over the `i` in the top left of a panel to get a short discription of it. - Tables can be filted. - You can inspect a specific cell's data in a table by click the eye icon on the end of the cell. - You can view seperate pages of results in tables with the pagination at the bottom. - Some tables will have more colums if you scroll to the right. # Proxy data If you would like to view the proxied data as the test are running please visit this dashboard. Mitmproxy Dashboard # Database If you would like to view the data this dash board uses, which is stored in a postgres database, please visit this dashboard. **Password is: postgres** Postgres Dasboard(Adminer) # Useful Commands - Run android tests `task android:test` - Run iOS tests `task ios:test` - Clear the database `task container:destroy` - Restore settings in case of an un-clean shutdown or frozen emulator `task restore` - Incase of unknown error `task clean` # Troubleshooting - If you data isn't showing, refresh the page.

panels.description: Test results for both iOS and Android. This only includes Appium tests, NOT data tests.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'passed')) as pass
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'passed') = 'true'
AND tr.info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_appium%'

SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'failed')) as fail
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'failed') = 'true'
AND tr.info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_appium%'

panels.description: Analytics calls captured. This is for all test runs stored in the postgres database.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT pr.info -> 'content' ->> 'batch' as batched_data
FROM proxy_request pr
JOIN test_results tr on tr.info ->> 'test_id' = pr.info ->> 'test_id'
JOIN test_id ti on ti.test_id = pr.info ->> 'test_id'
WHERE pr.info -> 'content' -> 'batch' IS NOT NULL

panels.title: Total: Analytics Calls (All test runs)

FROM proxy_response

panels.description: The total amount of test "runs", NOT the total amount of individual tests.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT test_results.info ->> 'test_id'
FROM test_results
GROUP BY test_results.info ->> 'test_id'

panels.description: The total amount of test "runs" for Android, NOT the total amount of individual tests.

SELECT tr.info ->> 'test_id'
FROM test_results tr
JOIN test_id ti ON ti.test_id = tr.info ->> 'test_id'
WHERE ti.platform = 'Android'
GROUP BY tr.info ->> 'test_id'

panels.description: The test id of the last run test.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT test_id
FROM test_id
ORDER BY timestamp DESC
LIMIT 1;

panels.title: Latest Test ID

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
  ROUND((tr.info ->> 'duration')::FLOAT) duration
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'Android'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'passed'
AND info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_data%'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
  ROUND((tr.info ->> 'duration')::FLOAT) duration
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'passed'
AND info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_data%'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,

FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'Android'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'failed'
AND info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_data%'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT

FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'failed'
AND info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_data'
ORDER BY 1

FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'Android'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'passed'

WHERE platform = 'IOS'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'passed'

SELECT

AND info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_appium%'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
  ROUND((tr.info ->> 'duration')::FLOAT) duration
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'failed'
AND info ->> 'node_id' LIKE '%::test_appium%'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT ti.platform,
pr.info ->> 'test_id' as test_id,
(tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
tr.info ->> 'outcome' as outcome,
(elem ->> 'properties') as properties
FROM proxy_request pr
JOIN test_results tr on tr.info ->> 'test_id' = pr.info ->> 'test_id'
JOIN test_id ti on ti.test_id = pr.info ->> 'test_id'
CROSS JOIN json_array_elements(CAST(pr.info -> 'content' ->> 'batch' AS json)) elem
WHERE pr.info -> 'content' -> 'batch' IS NOT NULL
AND elem -> 'properties' IS NOT NULL

SELECT ti.platform,
pr.info ->> 'test_id' as test_id,
(tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
tr.info ->> 'outcome' as outcome,
pr.info -> 'content' ->> 'batch' as batched_data
FROM proxy_request pr
JOIN test_results tr on tr.info ->> 'test_id' = pr.info ->> 'test_id'
JOIN test_id ti on ti.test_id = pr.info ->> 'test_id'
WHERE pr.info -> 'content' -> 'batch' IS NOT NULL

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info ->> 'test_id' as test_id,
  info ->> 'timestamp' as request_timestamp,
  info ->> 'host' as host,
  info ->> 'port' as port,
  info ->> 'method' as method,
  info ->> 'schema' as schema,
  info ->> 'authority' as authority,
  info ->> 'path' as path,
  info ->> 'http_version' as http_version,
  info ->> 'headers' as headers,
  info ->> 'content' as content,
  info ->> 'trailers' as trailers,
  info ->> 'timestamp_start' as timestamp_start,
  info ->> 'timestamp_end' as timestamp_end
FROM proxy_request
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info ->> 'test_id' as test_id,
  info ->> 'timestamp' as request_timestamp,
  info ->> 'http_version' as http_version,
  info ->> 'status_code' as status_code,
  info ->> 'reason' as reason,
  info ->> 'headers' as headers,
  info ->> 'content' as content,
  info ->> 'trailers' as trailers,
  info ->> 'timestamp_start' as timestamp_start,
  info ->> 'timestamp_end' as timestamp_end
FROM proxy_response
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info
FROM proxy_request
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info
FROM proxy_response
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1
